# WASM Workflow Rules

## public/wasm-pkg/ is committed to git
`public/wasm-pkg/` (NOT `src/wasm-pkg/`) is committed so Cloudflare Pages can
deploy without a Rust toolchain. `src/wasm-pkg/` is gitignored — ignore it.

## After ANY change to src-core/ Rust files you MUST:
1. Run `pnpm run build:wasm`
2. `git add public/wasm-pkg/`
3. Commit the updated wasm-pkg alongside your Rust changes

This applies to:
- New WASM bindings in `src-core/instrument-web/src/lib.rs`
- Cargo.toml dependency changes in any `src-core/` crate
- Version bumps in `package.json` or workspace `Cargo.toml` (version is embedded in WASM package.json)
- Any logic change in `src-core/instrument-core/`

## CI will fail if you skip this
The `wasm-sync` CI job runs `pnpm run build:wasm` and checks `git diff public/wasm-pkg/`.
If they differ, the job fails with: "public/wasm-pkg/ is out of sync with the Rust source."

## Diagnosing missing WASM in the browser
If a tool fails in the browser with **`"text/html" is not a valid JavaScript MIME type`**,
it means `public/wasm-pkg/instrument_web.js` is missing or was never built.
Vite returns `index.html` for any unmatched path, masking the real 404.
Fix: run `pnpm run build:wasm`.

## Vite 7 — never import() a /public path from source
Vite 7 forbids loading files under `public/` via `import()` from app source code.
It throws: "This file is in /public … should not be imported from source code."
The WASM loader in `src/bridge/web.ts` avoids this by building an absolute URL:
```ts
new URL(path, self.location.origin + '/')
```
and passing that string to `import()`. This makes the browser issue a plain fetch
that bypasses Vite's transform pipeline. `self` is used (not `window`) so the same
helper works in both the main thread and `regex.worker.ts`.
**Do not revert this to a root-relative path like `/wasm-pkg/instrument_web.js`.**

## Correct dev commands
- `pnpm run dev:web` — browser-only dev server (Vite only). Use this to test WASM/web behaviour.
- `pnpm tauri dev` — desktop app with hot reload.
- `pnpm dev` is an alias for `tauri dev` — do NOT use it to test web/WASM behaviour.

## instrument-core must stay pure
No `std::fs`, no `tauri`, no `tokio`, no `wasm-bindgen` in `src-core/instrument-core/`.
Run `pnpm run check:pure` to verify. Violations break the WASM build.

## sqlformat feature flag
`instrument-core` has an optional `sql` feature. `instrument-web/Cargo.toml` currently
enables it (`features = ["sql"]`). If excluding it, set `default-features = false`.
